Abstract

This document specifies the purpose, use cases, design principles, and base 
requirements for an Inventory Library.

I. Overview



II. Purpose

The purpose of the Inventory Library (IL) is to be able to maintain many items
items, with multiple owners, in an orderly fashion.

The goal of the IL is to allow multiple owners, be it members of the household
or friends (inventory borrowers in our case).

